annotationA: Thioredoxin-like; Disulfide oxidoreductase activity; protein disulfide oxidoreductase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: cellular response to DNA damage stimulus; cell redox homeostasis; glycerol ether metabolic process
annotationB: Proteasome subunit beta type-3; The proteasome is a multicatalytic proteinase complex which is characterized by its ability to cleave peptides with Arg, Phe, Tyr, Leu, and Glu adjacent to the leaving group at neutral or slightly basic pH. The proteasome has an ATP-dependent proteolytic activity
